<p style="font-size: 11pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><strong><br />
Dues</strong></span></p>
<p style="font-size: 10.5pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px;">As a new member, you will first see a prorated charge for the remainder of the current month. Thereafter, dues for the upcoming month are processed on the 24th of each month. If a payment fails for any reason, this gives people a few days to stay up-to-date. </span></p>
<p style="font-size: 10.5pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px;">For example, if you joined on April 2, and there are 30 days in April, the prorated amount is: </span></p>
<p style="font-size: 10.5pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px;">     (30 days- 2) x ($40 / 30 days) = 28 x 1.93 = $37.33</span></p>
<p style="font-size: 10.5pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px;">The first monthly payment would appear on April 24 for $40, and at that point you would be paid up through the end of May. </span></p>
